The most popular way of using MongoDB with Node and Express is with a library called Mongoose. 
Mongoose simplifies making MongoDB queries with its own library of methods.  
This means that we can connect mongoose directly to a MongoDB database and 
it will allow us to give more structure to our data with the addition of models and schemas.

Mongoose will act as a layer between our application and our database 
enabling us to do things like validate and run complex queries more effectively.

